@artmiamifairs is here! It’s a wonderful way to cap off an awesome 2022 and to look forward to exciting things coming in 2023. While I won’t be there in person this year, I’m honored that my work will be on view at Art Miami through Sunday (AM110). Thank you to my collectors, supporters, and the amazing team at @jonathanferraragallery for making this all possible. Just four years ago I was working in restaurants in Austin, TX hoping to build an art career after finishing my MFA. To be showing my work in Miami is a dream come true. Sincerely, thank you. ♥️ 

#kristinmoore #kristinmooreart #artmiami #jonathanferraragallery #miamiartweek #artworld #contemporarypainting

As many of you know, this piece was going to be in a group show in Oslo curated by @scottlistfield, @neilmperry, and @susannahkelly with @antlerpdx. Susannah passed away suddenly a few weeks ago. My heart goes out to Neil, their family and friends, and the teams at @talongallery and @antlerpdx. Neil and Susannah have created a truly special place in the art world. Susannah was not only a wonderful gallerist to work with, she was also a talented artist. She is very missed and it has taken time to process. Neil is continuing her legacy tonight and opening the “Wilderness” group show, along side Scott’s solo show “Symbols” in Portland at @antlerpdx. If you are local to Portland, please stop by the gallery tonight starting at 6pm to see the shows and share some memories of Susannah. You can email gallerist@antlerpdx.com for a list of all artworks in both shows. 

Thank you everyone for your support. Life is short, cherish what’s important and forget the rest. 🩵

One of the best burger spots in Dallas is also one of the oldest (going on 60+ years). I painted this from a photo I took back in 2022 on an evening drive home. This restaurant is twice as old as I am and has been frequented by three generations of my family over those decades. It means a lot for a restaurant to survive even 10 years, but 60+ is phenomenal. There’s something romantic about that, so I wanted to pay homage to it in this piece. Now I’m hungry. 

Acrylic on wood, 2023
36 x 36 inches
Private Collection
